               <msContents>
                  <summary>Apprenticeship contract made by a woman, Didyme, who specifies the number of yearly vacation days for the apprentice (18) and the obligation for him to recuperate the days eventually missed.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; back blank</note>
                     <note type="general">18 lines; broken left and top</note>
                     <note type="general">The main hand is minute and proficient. The last 6 lines are in a second hand, which is very large and fast</note>
                     <note type="general">The ink is faded</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
